irus outbreak has arrived in the Canary Islands. Crews in hazmat suits have begun the complicated task of screening and getting more than 100 passengers off the ship without potentially exposing themselves or the public to the virus. NBC’s Daniele Hamamdjian reports for Sunday TODAY.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510_S3_1920x1080-509wej.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:17:51 GMT</pubDate><title>Hantavirus-Plagued Cruise Arrives in Canary Islands</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 13:57:47 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Minyvonne Burke</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:00:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The recent coverage of a cruise ship hit with a deadly hantavirus outbreak is painfully familiar to cruisers who spent days and weeks trapped in their cabins at the start of the Covid-19 pandemic in 2020</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/covid-19-cruise-passengers-recall-painful-memories-hantavirus-outbreak-rcna343826</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/covid-19-cruise-passengers-recall-painful-memories-hantavirus-outbreak-rcna343826</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-covid-cruise-ch-1100-06bed0.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Jeff Greenberg</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Covid cruise.</media:text><media:description type="plain">A row of cruise ships docked in Miami in 2020 due to the coronavirus outbreak.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260503-hantavirus-cruise-safrica-ww-1855-2735c0.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>AFP via Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A blue and white cruise ship floats in calm waters under a clear blue sky.</media:text><media:description type="plain">A row of cruise ships docked in Miami in 2020 due to the coronavirus outbreak.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-covid-cruise-ch-1101-7b2b0d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Tim Rue</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Covid cruise.</media:text><media:description type="plain">A row of cruise ships docked in Miami in 2020 due to the coronavirus outbreak.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-covid-cruise-ch-1100-06bed0.jpg" height="1666" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Covid-19 cruise passengers recall painful memories amid hantavirus outbreak</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:00:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Nollaig O&#39;Connor</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:00:53 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Even after more than 100 passengers and crewmembers fell sick during a norovirus outbreak aboard the Caribbean Princess cruise ship, passenger Jan van Milligen said life on board still felt surprisingly normal.“The normal atmosphere is still here,” van Milligen, who has spent the last 21 days aboard the ship with relatives and friends from South Africa, told NBC News on Saturday.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/caribbean/norovirus-outbreak-princess-cruise-caribbean-rcna344359</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/caribbean/norovirus-outbreak-princess-cruise-caribbean-rcna344359</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Caribbean-Princess-ch-1448-8e67d8.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Ivan Pisarenko</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Caribbean Princess.</media:text><media:description type="plain">The outbreak sickened 102 of the ship’s 3,116 passengers and 13 crewmembers, according to the CDC.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Caribbean-Princess-ch-1448-8e67d8.jpg" height="1666" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:00:53 GMT</pubDate><title>More than 100 sickened in norovirus outbreak aboard Caribbean Princess cruise</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:00:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Mithil Aggarwal</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:30:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Love of Diet Coke runs deep for Ishika Gupta, but it was the fear of losing her favorite drink that took the obsession to new heights</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/asia/diet-coke-parties-india-aluminum-can-shortage-rcna343993</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/asia/diet-coke-parties-india-aluminum-can-shortage-rcna343993</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-rs-8a5491.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Courtesy of Ishika Gupta</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ishika Gupta&#39;s Diet Coke party.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ishika Gupta’s Diet Coke-themed party in Delhi, India, on April 26.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-comp-rs-b0e30f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Courtesy of Ishika Gupta</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Gupta’s party was a success with Gen Z, who she says are craving more alcohol-free experiences.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ishika Gupta’s Diet Coke-themed party in Delhi, India, on April 26.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-5-rs-6aad0d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Courtesy of Ishika Gupta</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Tickets for the party sold out, with around 150 people in attendance.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ishika Gupta’s Diet Coke-themed party in Delhi, India, on April 26.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-diet-coke-rs-8a5491.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:30:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Diet Coke parties are all the rage in India as aluminum can shortage bubbles up</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:30:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 13:29:51 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Energy Secretary Chris Wright tells Meet the Press that the Trump administration’s priority is ending Iran’s nuclear program and restoring secure shipping through the Strait of Hormuz, while ongoing tensions could keep gas prices elevated in the short term.</description><expires>2056-05-10T13:28:39.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">mtp_full_wright_260510</guid><link>http